OL,3,CChief warns firefighters do not have
OL,4,Cenough kit to do jobs safely
OL,6,FJersey's Chief Fire Officer has warned
OL,7,Fthat the Service does not have enough
OL,8,Fkit to protect firefighters as well as
OL,9,Fthey can.
OL,11,FPaul Brown, who has led the Jersey
OL,12,FFire and Rescue Service since 2019,
OL,13,Fsays that firefighters do not
OL,14,Fcurrently have enough personal
OL,15,Fprotective equipment (PPE) to do their
OL,16,Fjobs safely, according to World Health
OL,17,FOrganization (WHO) guidelines.
OL,19,FSince 2022, the WHO has designated
OL,20,Fbeing a firefighter as a carcinogenic
OL,21,For cancer-causing occupation.
