OL,3,CChief warns firefighters do not have
OL,4,Cenough kit to do jobs safely
OL,6,FProfessor John Cherrie, from the
OL,7,FInstitute of Occupational Medicine,
OL,8,Fexplains: "Firefighters are at risk of
OL,9,Fexposure to chemicals which cause
OL,10,Fcancer through dust, their suits,
OL,11,Ffirefighting equipment, and asbestos
OL,12,Fin buildings.
OL,14,F"A fire is a very unnatural
OL,15,Fenvironment, and the only real way
OL,16,Ffirefighters can be protected is by
OL,17,Fusing personal protective equipment."
OL,19,FAccording to the WHO, firefighters
OL,20,Frequire two different sets of PPE each
OL,21,Fto remain safe.
